#import "/_lib/0.1.1.typ": *
#show: template

#taxon[Definition]
#title[Morphism of ringed spaces]

A _morphism_ of #local("008E")[ringed spaces] $(X,Oo_(X))$ and $(Y, Oo_(Y))$
is a continous map $pi : X ->  Y$, together with a #link("00AK")[morphism of sheaves] $pi^(hash) : Oo_Y -> pi_(**) Oo _(X)$

$pi_(**) Oo _(X) $ is the pushforward given by $Uu |-> Oo _(X) (pi^(-1)( Uu)) $.


